description: Frontend standards for Svelte + reusable UI + scoped SCSS
globs: web/src/**/*.svelte
alwaysApply: false
---

## Component design (Svelte)
- Prefer reusable components for UI.
- Components should be dumb by default: render/compose UI and delegate state + side effects to stores/services.
- Keep each component focused on one responsibility (one thing it “knows” / “does”).

## Styling (SCSS modules)
- Use SCSS modules when Sass is enabled.
- Target structure: component-scoped SCSS (module-scoped styles) and avoid global selectors.
- Avoid growing components just to fit styling—extract reusable subcomponents and/or shared style tokens.

## “When in doubt”
- Ask me before changing global layout, routing, or auth/db behavior.
